Features

User authentication using JWT and bcrypt
File upload functionality with Multer
Responsive frontend built with React and Tailwind CSS
API requests handled with Axios
Real-time development with Vite and Nodemon

Technologies Used
Backend

Node.js with Express for the server
TypeScript for type-safe code
JWT (jsonwebtoken) for authentication
Bcrypt for password hashing
Multer for file uploads
Morgan for request logging
CORS for cross-origin resource sharing
Inversify for dependency injection
Reflect-metadata for metadata-driven development

Frontend

React with Vite for fast development and building
Tailwind CSS for styling
React Router for client-side routing
Axios for API requests
Lucide React for icons
Sonner for toast notifications
ESLint for code linting

Prerequisites
Ensure you have the following installed:

Node.js (v18 or higher)
npm (v9 or higher)
Git (for cloning the repository)
A code editor like VS Code

Setup Instructions
Backend Setup

Clone the repository:git clone <your-github-repo-link>
cd server


Install dependencies:npm install


Create a .env file in the server directory with the following variables:PORT=5000
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret

Replace your_jwt_secret with a secure secret key for JWT.
Build the project:npm run build


Run the development server (uses Nodemon for hot reloading):npm run dev

The backend will run on http://localhost:5000 (or the port specified in .env).

Frontend Setup

Navigate to the client directory:cd client


Install dependencies:npm install


Create a .env file in the client directory with the following:VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000

This points the frontend to the backend API.
Run the development server:npm run dev

The frontend will run on http://localhost:5173 (default Vite port).

Running the Application

Start the backend:
In the server directory, run:npm run dev




Start the frontend:
In the client directory, run:npm run dev




Open your browser and navigate to http://localhost:5173 to view the application.

Accessing the Deployed Version
The live version of the project is hosted at:[Insert live link here, e.g., https://your-project-name.vercel.app]
Ensure the backend is also deployed (e.g., on Render, Heroku, or another platform) and update the VITE_API_URL in the frontend's .env file to point to the deployed backend API.
